Package org.apache.freemarker.core

The most commonly used API-s of FreeMarker; start with Configuration (see also the Getting Stared in the Manual.)

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CustomStateScope
    An object that's a scope that can store custom state objects.
    DirectiveCallPlace
    Gives information about the place where a directive is called from, also lets you attach a custom data object to that place.
    LocalContext
    An interface that represents a local context.
    ParsingAndProcessingConfiguration
    Don't implement this interface yourself; use the existing implementation(s).
    ParsingConfiguration
    Implemented by FreeMarker core classes (not by you) that provide configuration settings that affect template parsing (as opposed to (Object, Writer) template processing).
    ProcessingConfiguration
    Implemented by FreeMarker core classes (not by you) that provide configuration settings that affect template processing (as opposed to template parsing).
    TemplateClassResolver
    Used by built-ins and other template language features that get a class based on a string.
    TemplateExceptionHandler
    Used for the template_exception_handler configuration setting; see MutableProcessingConfiguration.setTemplateExceptionHandler(TemplateExceptionHandler) for more.
    TopLevelConfiguration
    Implemented by FreeMarker core classes (not by you) that provide Configuration-level settings.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Configuration
    The main entry point into the FreeMarker API; encapsulates the configuration settings of FreeMarker, also serves as a central template-loading and caching service.
    Configuration.Builder
    Creates a new Configuration, with the setting specified in this object.
    Configuration.ExtendableBuilder<SelfT extends Configuration.ExtendableBuilder<SelfT>>
    Usually you use Configuration.Builder instead of this abstract class, except where you declare the type of a method parameter or field, where the more generic Configuration.ExtendableBuilder should be used.
    CustomStateKey<T>
    Used with CustomStateScope-s; each subclass must have exactly one instance, which should be stored in a static final field.
    Environment
    Object that represents the runtime environment during template processing.
    MutableParsingAndProcessingConfiguration<SelfT extends MutableParsingAndProcessingConfiguration<SelfT>>  
    MutableProcessingConfiguration<SelfT extends MutableProcessingConfiguration<SelfT>>
    Extended by FreeMarker core classes (not by you) that support specifying ProcessingConfiguration setting values.
    Template
    Stores an already parsed template, ready to be processed (rendered) for unlimited times, possibly from multiple threads.
    TemplateConfiguration
    A partial set of configuration settings used for customizing the Configuration-level settings for individual Template-s (or rather, for a group of templates).
    TemplateConfiguration.Builder  
    TemplateLanguage
    Represents a template language.
    Version
    Represents a version number plus the further qualifiers and build info.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AutoEscapingPolicy
    Used as the value of the autoEscapingPolicy setting.
    NamingConvention
    Used as the value of the ParsingConfiguration.getNamingConvention() namingConvention} setting.
    TagSyntax
    Used as the value of the ParsingConfiguration.getTagSyntax() tagSyntax} setting.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CallPlaceCustomDataInitializationException
    Thrown by DirectiveCallPlace.getOrCreateCustomData(Object, org.apache.freemarker.core.util.ObjectFactory)
    ConfigurationException
    Error while configuring FreeMarker.
    CoreSettingValueNotSetException
    Thrown when you try to read a core (that is, non-custom) configuration setting which wasn't set and isn't inherited from a parent object and has no default either.
    CustomSettingValueNotSetException
    Thrown by ProcessingConfiguration.getCustomSetting(Serializable) if the custom setting is not set.
    InvalidReferenceException
    A subclass of TemplateException that says that an FTL expression has evaluated to null or it refers to something that doesn't exist.
    InvalidSettingNameException
    Thrown by Configuration.ExtendableBuilder.setSetting(String, String) if the setting name was not recognized.
    InvalidSettingValueException
    Thrown by Configuration.ExtendableBuilder.setSetting(String, String); The setting name was recognized, but its value couldn't be parsed or the setting couldn't be set for some other reason.
    NestedContentNotSupportedException
    Used in custom TemplateDirectiveModel-s to check if the directive invocation has no body.
    NonBooleanException
    Indicates that a TemplateBooleanModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonDateException
    Indicates that a TemplateDateModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonExtendedHashException
    Indicates that a TemplateHashModelEx value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonExtendedNodeException
    Indicates that a TemplateNodeModelEx value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonHashException
    Indicates that a TemplateHashModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonMarkupOutputException
    Indicates that a TemplateMarkupOutputModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonMethodException
    Indicates that a TemplateMethodModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonNodeException
    Indicates that a TemplateNodeModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonNumericalException
    Indicates that a TemplateNumberModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonSequenceException
    Indicates that a TemplateSequenceModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonSequenceOrCollectionException
    Indicates that a TemplateSequenceModel or TemplateCollectionModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    NonStringException
    Indicates that a TemplateScalarModel value was expected (or maybe something that can be automatically coerced to that), but the value had a different type.
    NonStringOrTemplateOutputException
    Indicates that a TemplateScalarModel (or maybe something that can be automatically coerced to that) or TemplateMarkupOutputModel value was expected, but the value had a different type.
    ParseException
    Parsing-time exception in a template (as opposed to a runtime exception, a TemplateException).
    SettingValueNotSetException
    Thrown when you try to read a configuration setting which wasn't set and isn't inherited from a parent object and has no default either.
    StopException
    This exception is thrown when a #stop directive is encountered.
    TemplateException
    Runtime exception in a template (as opposed to a parsing-time exception: ParseException).
    TemplateNotFoundException
    Thrown when Configuration.getTemplate(String) (or similar) doesn't find a template.
    UnexpectedTypeException
    The type of a value differs from what was expected.
    WrongTemplateCharsetException
    Thrown by the Template constructors that specify a non-null encoding whoch doesn't match the encoding specified in the #ftl header of the template.
